T*
(On this tiny ReLU MLP, both tools were able to answer the same robustness question.) Tj
T*
(Marabou gave a very direct logical encoding style: I could loop over target classes and) Tj
T*
(add inequalities by hand. alpha-beta-CROWN required more configuration work, especially) Tj
T*
(for the custom EMNIST data loader, but once the YAML and loader were correct it produced) Tj
T*
(a compact verified/falsified summary and handled both attack and bound-based) Tj
T*
(verification in one pipeline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The biggest strength I saw in alpha-beta-CROWN is that it combines fast adversarial) Tj
T*
(search with bound propagation and branch-and-bound. For the unsafe epsilon 0.2 case, it) Tj
T*
(found a counterexample in under half a second. For the safe epsilon 0.02 case, the) Tj
T*
(initial CROWN bounds were already strong enough to prove robustness. The limitation is) Tj
T*
(that custom experiments are sensitive to model/data format details: unsupported config) Tj
T*
(keys, path substitution, and custom loader return shapes caused setup issues that had to) Tj
T*
(be debugged. Overall, alpha-beta-CROWN felt more scalable and experiment-oriented, while) Tj
T*
(Marabou felt more explicit and lower-level.) Tj
